public abstract class InverterProvider
extends java.lang.Object
implements FullJtapiTpi

This is an Generic JTAPI "raw" Telephony Provider that wraps a JTAPI Provider and allows the Generic JTAPI Framework to act as a decorator to a JTAPI Provider. Creation date: (2000-05-31 17:42:58)

getTerminals

public TermData[] getTerminals()
                        throws javax.telephony.ResourceUnavailableException
Get a list of available terminals. This may be null if the Telephony (raw) Provider does not support Terminals. If the Terminal set it too large, this will throw a ResourceUnavailableException

Since we went to lazy connecting between Addresses and Terminals, this is called so we don't have to follow all Address->Terminal associations to get the full set of Terminals. Creation date: (2000-02-11 12:29:00)

Returns:
An array of terminal names, media type containers.
Throws:
javax.telephony.ResourceUnavailableException - if the set it too large to be returned dynamically.

initialize

public void initialize(java.util.Map props)
                throws javax.telephony.ProviderUnavailableException
Initialize the Inverter Provider with a Map that defines which real JTAPI implementation to load beneath me. This consists of two properties:
  • PeerClassName That defines the PeerClass name passed into the JtapiPeerFactory
  • ProviderString That defines the provider service string passed into the JtapiPeer to create the provider.
If "replace" is a map property, then the passed in map replaces instead of augmenting the default properties map.
Tags copied from interface: CoreTpi
Parameters:
props - The name value properties map
